Lab Description: Customer Behavior Analysis & Predictive Modeling

This lab focuses on analyzing a customer dataset and building a predictive model to understand and forecast customer spending behavior. The main goals of the lab include data cleaning, exploration, and evaluation of a regression model.

Key Steps:
	1.	Data Cleaning and Preprocessing
	•	Removed duplicate rows to ensure data integrity.
	•	Filled missing numeric values with the mean for consistent calculations.
	•	Standardized column names by converting to lowercase, replacing spaces with underscores, and removing punctuation for easier reference in code.
	2.	Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
	•	Inspected basic statistics and data types.
	•	Identified numeric and categorical columns.
	•	Visualized relationships between features and target variable (Yearly Amount Spent) to identify trends and correlations.
	3.	Modeling
	•	Split the dataset into training and testing sets.
	•	Built a regression model to predict customer yearly spending based on features such as session length, app usage, website usage, and length of membership.
	4.	Model Evaluation
	•	Assessed model performance using metrics including:
	•	Mean Absolute Error (MAE) – average absolute difference between predicted and actual values.
	•	Mean Squared Error (MSE) – average squared difference between predicted and actual values.
	•	R² Score – proportion of variance explained by the model.

Outcome:

This lab demonstrates the complete workflow of data preprocessing, cleaning, and regression analysis. Students learn how to handle missing data, standardize datasets for modeling, and evaluate predictions using standard regression metrics.
